GREATER CHINA DAYBOOK: Alibaba’s Dispute With Yahoo; Pork Prices Increase

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-15T23:37:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/greater-china-daybook-eu-anti-subsidy-duties-alibaba-s-spinoff-lawful-.html
Alibaba Group Holding Ltd. Chairman
Jack Ma said the spinoff of the Alipay online payment business
is “lawful” and “transparent,” after largest shareholder
Yahoo! Inc. claimed it wasn’t consulted on the transfer.  Alibaba said it and its biggest shareholders, Yahoo and
Softbank Corp., are “engaged in and committed to” resolving
issues related to Alipay.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  